Sentencas: Co is doped to Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6 to enhance its electrochemical activity as the cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Effect of Co doping on the electrochemical properties of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6 electrode for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Pure cubic perovsldtes of Sr(2)Fet(1.5-x)Co(x)Mo(0.5)O(6) (SF1.5-xCxM, x = 0, 0.5, 1) are synthesized using a glycine-nitrate combustion progress.
Titulo: Effect of Co doping on the electrochemical properties of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6 electrode for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The average thermal expansion coefficient varies from 15.8 to 19.8 x 10(-6)K(-1).
Titulo: Effect of Co doping on the electrochemical properties of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6 electrode for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity increases while its activation energy decreases with increasing Co content.
Titulo: Effect of Co doping on the electrochemical properties of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6 electrode for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy analysis demonstrates mixed valences of Fe, Co and Mo, suggesting small polaron hopping mechanism.
Titulo: Effect of Co doping on the electrochemical properties of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6 electrode for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Electrical conductivity relaxation (ECR) measurement shows that the surface exchange coefficient increases about two orders of magnitude when the content increases from x = 0 to x = 1.0, i.e. from 2.55 x 10(-5) to 2.20 x 10(-3) cm s(-1) at 750 degrees C. ECR also exhibits that chemical diffusion coefficient increases with Co content.
Titulo: Effect of Co doping on the electrochemical properties of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6 electrode for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Density Functional Theory calculation demonstrates that oxygen vacancy formation energy decreases with Co content, suggesting high oxygen vacancy concentration at high Co content.
Titulo: Effect of Co doping on the electrochemical properties of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6 electrode for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Impedance spectroscopy on symmetric cells consisting of SF1.5-xCxM electrodes and La(0.8)Sr(0.2)Oa(0.3)Mg(0.2)O(3-delta) electrolytes shows that Co doping is very effective in reducing the interfacial polarization resistance, from 0.105 Omega cm(2) to 0.056 Omega cm(2) at 750 degrees
Titulo: Effect of Co doping on the electrochemical properties of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6 electrode for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: C. These results suggest that Co doping into Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6 can substantially improve its electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Effect of Co doping on the electrochemical properties of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6 electrode for solid oxide fuel cell
